table_description:
data_description: This table contains completed evaluation records for soundbox customer interactions within the MHD (Mobile/Merchant Help Desk) system. It stores daily aggregated metrics including active sessions count, analyzed sessions count, evaluation completion status, customer feedback (happy/sad), and agent handover ticket counts. The table includes a date dimension and customer entity filtering capability (cst_entity field), allowing for time-series analysis of soundbox evaluation performance. Each record represents evaluation metrics for soundbox interactions on a given date for specific customer entity profiles.

business_description: This table supports the MHD evaluation dashboard by providing key performance indicators for soundbox customer service operations. It enables monitoring of customer satisfaction through feedback rates, tracking evaluation completion rates, and measuring agent handover percentages. Business stakeholders use this data to assess soundbox support quality, identify trends in customer satisfaction, optimize agent workload distribution, and make data-driven decisions to improve customer service operations. The table serves as a foundation for performance reporting, quality assurance, and operational efficiency analysis within the soundbox product ecosystem.

data_description: This table contains comprehensive evaluation metrics for AI-powered customer service interactions, specifically tracking LLM (Large Language Model) performance at Level 1. The table stores aggregated conversation data including session counts, evaluation scores, response relevance ratings, empathy measurements, sentiment analysis results, and various failure mode indicators. Key data categories include conversation quality metrics (eval scores, response relevance, empathy), customer satisfaction indicators (MSAT, sentiment changes), operational metrics (active sessions, resolution rates), and error tracking (intent detection failures, bot repetition, function call failures, topic drift). The data is segmented by problem descriptions and customer service entity types.

business_description: This table supports the evaluation and monitoring of AI customer service bot performance, particularly for soundbox products and AI bot interactions. It enables business teams to track customer satisfaction, conversation quality, and identify areas where the AI systems are failing or performing well. The metrics help in optimizing AI responses, improving customer experience, and ensuring quality control in automated customer service. Business stakeholders can use this data to measure the effectiveness of AI implementations, identify training needs for the models, track sentiment improvements, and monitor resolution rates across different problem categories. This supports continuous improvement of AI-powered customer support systems.
